Title : Arbore Church
Text : [[File:Biserica Arbore12.jpg|thumb|Arbore Church]]
The '''Arbore Church''' ({{lang-ro|Biserica Arbore}}) is a [[Romanian Orthodox]] monastery church in [[Arbore]] Commune, [[Suceava County]], [[Romania]]. Built in 1502 by [[Luca Arbore]], and dedicated to the [[Beheading of St. John the Baptist]], it is one of eight buildings that make up the [[churches of Moldavia]] [[UNESCO World Heritage Site]].<ref>[http://whc.unesco.org/en/list/598 Churches of Moldavia] at the UNESCO site</ref> It is also listed as a [[Monument istoric|historic monument]] by the country's [[Ministry of Culture and Religious Affairs (Romania)|Ministry of Culture and Religious Affairs]].<ref>{{ro icon}} [http://www.patrimoniu.ro/images/LMI/LMI-2010_SV.pdf Lista Monumentelor Istorice 2010: Jude≈£ul Suceava], p.2162</ref>

